    • Constructor Detail

      • ValidationException

        public ValidationException(String message,
                   RuleException exception,
                   long exceptionOffset,
                   Object... reasons)
        Creates an exception with a specified message and optional reason varargs based on an existing exception. The existing exception is thrown by a validation rule. An offset is used to indicate the position of the invalid value in dependence to the message representation (e.g. byte position, if a byte representation is used).
        Parameters:
        message - the specified exception message
        exception - the existing exception, which has to be encapsulated
        exceptionOffset - the position of the invalid value
        reasons - the optional reasons, which let to the exception
